cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with deep learning for plant diseases classification, which is a computer vision task, hence it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper proposes a new architecture for plant diseases classification that leverages multitask learning, which is a common technique in machine learning, hence it is also likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also mentions the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are a popular type of deep learning models, hence it is also likely to belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper proposes a new method for visualizing the most important image regions for classification, which is a form of information retrieval, hence it is also likely to belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of communication between two deep classifiers, which is a form of neural network architecture, hence it is also likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
